			======================================
				 Installing RedirFS
				   A Quick Guide
			======================================

1. Requirements
	
	* Running Linux kernel version 2.6.x
	* Source code for running Linux kernel
	* Linux kernel compiled with modules support

2. Download
	
	* Get the latest stable version at http://www.redirfs.org/packages/redirfs-x.y.tar.gz

3. Compilation
	
	* Unpack package
		$ tar -xvzf redirfs-x.y.tar.gz

	* Change to the redirfs-x.y directory
		$ cd redirfs-x.y

	* Run make command
		$ make -C /lib/modules/`uname -r`/build M=`pwd` modules

4. Inserting module

	* Change user to root
		$ su

	* Insert redirfs.ko module
		# insmod redirfs.ko

5. Problems & Bugs

	* Can be reported to Bugzilla at http://www.redirfs.org/cgi-bin/bugzilla/index.cgi
